{"title":"LLC 2025 Hallek","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/LLC 2025 Hallek iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"LEUCEMIA\\NLINFOCÍTICA CRÓNICA\\N(LLC) — Update 2025","guid":"06no-ou0MPyN2DNZ9jqUWg","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"DEFINICIÓN Y\\NEPIDEMIOLOGÍA","guid":"WcLzMhjygFnt_8BKGeOyOg","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Neoplasia de linfocitos B maduros clonales CD5+","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Leucemia MÁS FRECUENTE del adulto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"= Linfoma linfocítico pequeño (SLL) → solo linfonodo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Incidencia 4.6/100.000 hab/año (SEER)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"Mediana edad al diagnóstico → 70 AÑOS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Relación hombre:mujer 1.9:1","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"<10% pacientes <45 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"Sobrevida relativa 5 años → 88.5% (2024)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"1","text":"Mortalidad en descenso continuo últimas 2 décadas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"1","text":"Incidencia menor en asiáticos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"12","parent":"0","text":"PATOGÉNESIS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"Origen → célula madre hematopoyética (HSC)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"12","text":"Proliferación clonal + acumulación de linfocitos B maduros CD5+","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"12","text":"Localización → sangre, médula ósea, ganglios, bazo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"12","text":"Transformación\\Nleucemogénica\\Nescalonada","guid":"_x1yB6uWHIjk8rvxHOOGPA","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"Pérdida/adición cromosómica inicial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"16","text":"Mutaciones adicionales → mayor agresividad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"19","parent":"12","text":"ALTERACIONES CROMOSÓMICAS\\N(80% pacientes ≥1)","guid":"BbQZ4TFSgss1oh8kc1wEAA","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"del(13q14) →\\N55% de casos","guid":"A-WmjTHSFzNti1bQvpOyMA","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"MÁS FRECUENTE","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"Aislada = forma MENOS agresiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"20","text":"miR-15a y miR-16-1 → regulan apoptosis/ciclo celular","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"19","text":"Trisomía 12 →\\N10-20%","guid":"LsBT8YyOKIbvaGvkUwPSzA","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"Pronóstico INTERMEDIO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"Genes implicados desconocidos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"19","text":"del(11q) →\\N10-25%","guid":"-UXwqjc6yDa7794vC4kMVA","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"Gen ATM (kinasa respuesta a daño DNA)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"27","text":"Adenopatías VOLUMINOSAS","guid":"oQLIr23mRF9lbHVSYkZzbw","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"27","text":"Progresión rápida, SG reducida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"27","text":"Parcialmente superado por inmunoquimioterapia (FCR)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"32","parent":"19","text":"del(17p) →\\N5-8% naïve","guid":"wtqURApYVycJMi_QJ0qwLg","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"Gen TP53 (supresor tumoral)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"RESISTENCIA a quimioterapia genotóxica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":">80% con del(17p) tienen mut TP53 alelo restante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"32","text":"PEOR PRONÓSTICO","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"19","text":"mut TP53 sin del(17p) → efecto deletéreo similar","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"12","text":"PAISAJE\\NGENÓMICO\\N(WES)","guid":"6N7O3BQo6Vvpo3lgvG-gRQ","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"44 genes recurrentemente mutados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"11 variaciones somáticas de número de copias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"38","text":"Genes clave → NOTCH1, MYD88, TP53, ATM, SF3B1, FBXW7, POT1","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"38","text":"Vías centrales → procesamiento RNA, actividad MYC, señalización MAPK","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"12","text":"Estado\\Nmutacional\\NIGHV","guid":"gjfCXNefaioY4BDvcjaSkg","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"IGHV MUTADO → mejor pronóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"43","text":"IGHV NO MUTADO → peor pronóstico, más agresivo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"12","text":"MICROAMBIENTE\\Ntumoral","guid":"c-ec_bqvJO60x9ACGn0OZA","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"Macrófagos, fibroblastos, células T, células dendríticas foliculares","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"46","text":"Quimioquinas, citoquinas, factores angiogénicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"46","text":"Señalización de supervivencia vía BCR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"46","text":"DIANA terapéutica de nuevos inhibidores","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"0","text":"DIAGNÓSTICO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"Criterios\\NiwCLL","guid":"R9O4Gra8Pk1d5xlkT6YMqA","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"≥5.000 linfocitos B/µL en sangre periférica ≥3 meses","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"Clonalidad confirmada por CITOMETRÍA DE FLUJO","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"51","text":"Frotis\\Nsanguíneo","guid":"SzdkVla_LDyUQQi3d5PCHg","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"Linfocitos pequeños maduros","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"55","text":"Núcleo denso sin nucléolos discernibles","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"55","text":"Cromatina parcialmente agregada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"55","text":"Sombras de Gumprecht (smudge cells)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"55","text":"Prolinfocitos <55% (si >55% → LPL-B)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"51","text":"INMUNOFENOTIPO\\NDIAGNÓSTICO","guid":"3SxGZe5neyq0zEkud8VxBg","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"Panel esencial → CD19+, CD5+, CD20+ (bajo), CD23+","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"Ig superficie baja, restricción kappa O lambda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"61","text":"CD79b bajo (vs normal en célula B sana)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"61","text":"Casos borderline → CD43, CD79b, CD81, CD200, CD10, ROR1","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"66","parent":"51","text":"Diagnóstico\\Ndiferencial","guid":"C6URsMbP6hNOQt_BtA_40Q","children":[{"id":"67","parent":"66","text":"Linfocitosis B monoclonal (MBL)\\N→ <5.000 linf B/µL","guid":"ty27i9X5EfYXTIPUZM-TJw","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Sin adenopatías/organomegalia/citopenias/síntomas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"Progresa a LLC 1-2%/año","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"70","parent":"66","text":"Linfoma linfocítico pequeño (SLL) → adenopatías sin linfocitosis","guid":"","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"Biopsia ganglionar para confirmar","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"66","text":"Linfoma del manto → CD5+ pero CD23-, ciclina D1+","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"66","text":"Excluir → infección, autoinmune","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"74","parent":"51","text":"Clasificación\\NOMS 5ª edición","guid":"fLKZg2NgQxgZI5h7hF-F2A","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"Neoplasias B maduras → proliferaciones linfocíticas pequeñas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"74","text":"Familia MBL y LLC/SLL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"74","text":"T-CLL ya NO existe → T-PLL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"74","text":"LPL-B ya NO es entidad reconocida","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"0","text":"ESTRATIFICACIÓN\\NDE RIESGO","guid":"xLmNMegp1dRpTaSXvyo2jw","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":"FISH → del(13q), trisomía 12, del(11q), del(17p)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"79","text":"mut TP53 → SIEMPRE solicitar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"79","text":"del(17p) + mut TP53 = DISFUNCIÓN TP53 → clave para decisión terapéutica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"79","text":"Carga Ig pesada → cadena pesada variable (IGHV)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"Mutado vs no mutado","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"85","parent":"0","text":"ESTADIFICACIÓN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"Sistema RAI\\N(modificado)","guid":"DQMM3HE6KormQDjx8fgi3Q","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"Riesgo bajo (ex Rai 0) → linfocitosis aislada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"Riesgo intermedio (ex Rai I-II) → linfocitosis + adenopatías ± esplenomegalia/hepatomegalia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"86","text":"Riesgo alto (ex Rai III-IV) → Hb <11 g/dL ó plaquetas <100×10⁹/L","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"90","parent":"85","text":"Sistema\\NBINET","guid":"-R75YmbQc1ve5s7IY8x8wQ","children":[{"id":"91","parent":"90","text":"Estadio A → Hb ≥10, plaquetas ≥100, ≤2 áreas afectadas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"90","text":"Estadio B → Hb ≥10, plaquetas ≥100, ≥3 áreas afectadas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"90","text":"Estadio C → Hb <10 ó plaquetas <100","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"90","text":"5 áreas → cabeza/cuello, axilas, ingles, bazo, hígado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"85","text":"CLL-IPI (Índice\\NPronóstico Internacional)","guid":"cRkujSQZpW5-vp9uKXMB-w","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"5 factores ponderados","guid":"","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"Disfunción TP53 (del17p/mut)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"96","text":"IGHV no mutado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"96","text":"β2-microglobulina sérica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"96","text":"Estadio clínico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"96","text":"Edad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"102","parent":"95","text":"4 grupos → bajo, intermedio, alto, muy alto riesgo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"95","text":"SLP 3 años con terapia dirigida → 96.5%, 87.6%, 82.4%, 78.7%","guid":"","children":[{"id":"104","parent":"103","text":"Mantiene valor pronóstico en era de agentes dirigidos","guid":"dUxTV5TsDqBNlEvjhBkINw","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"95","text":"SG 3 años con terapia dirigida → 100%, 96%, 93.9%, 89.4%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"106","parent":"85","text":"IPS-E (para estadios tempranos asintomáticos)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"IGHV no mutado + linfocitos >15×10⁹/L + ganglios palpables","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"106","text":"Riesgo acumulado 5 años de iniciar tratamiento → 8.4%, 28.4%, 61.2%","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"0","text":"INDICACIÓN DE TRATAMIENTO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"110","parent":"109","text":"Enfermedad INACTIVA (Binet A-B, Rai 0-II) → OBSERVAR (watch and wait)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"Múltiples estudios NO muestran beneficio de tratar precoz","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"110","text":"Incluye estudios con QT, inmuno-QT e ibrutinib","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"113","parent":"109","text":"Enfermedad ACTIVA/SINTOMÁTICA → criterios iwCLL","guid":"","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"Falla medular progresiva → Hb <10 ó plaquetas <100","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"113","text":"Esplenomegalia masiva (≥6 cm bajo reborde costal izq) o progresiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"113","text":"Adenopatías masivas (≥10 cm) o progresivas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"113","text":"Linfocitosis progresiva → aumento ≥50% en 2 meses ó duplicación <6 meses","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"113","text":"Complicaciones autoinmunes refractarias a corticoides","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"113","text":"Compromiso extranodal sintomático (piel, riñón, pulmón, columna)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"113","text":"Síntomas B → pérdida peso ≥10%, fatiga severa (ECOG ≥2), fiebre ≥38°C ≥2 sem, sudoración nocturna ≥1 mes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"121","parent":"109","text":"Hipogammaglobulinemia aislada NO indica tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"109","text":"Linfocitosis aislada NO indica tratamiento (leucostasis rara en LLC)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"123","parent":"0","text":"EVALUACIÓN DE RESPUESTA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"124","parent":"123","text":"Categorías → RC, RP, enfermedad estable, progresión, refractariedad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"123","text":"Enfermedad Residual Mínima (ERM)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"IMPORTANCIA CRECIENTE en decisiones terapéuticas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"125","text":"ERM indetectable (uMRD) → <1 célula LLC/10.000 leucocitos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"125","text":"Técnicas → citometría flujo 6 colores, PCR ASO, ClonoSEQ (NGS)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"125","text":"Panel citometría → CD19, CD20, CD5, CD43, CD79b, CD81","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"125","text":"uMRD en RC o RP → mejor SLP que dMRD en RC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"125","text":"uMRD 1L → SLP 10 años 65% vs 10% (dMRD)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"125","text":"Guía duración tratamiento con inhibidores dirigidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"125","text":"CIRI → índice individualizado continuo de riesgo","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"134","parent":"0","text":"TRATAMIENTO DE PRIMERA LÍNEA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"PRINCIPIO → solo tratar enfermedad activa/sintomática o estadios avanzados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"134","text":"Fitness del paciente YA NO determina elección (con agentes dirigidos)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"134","text":"SIN del(17p)/mut TP53","guid":"","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"IGHV MUTADO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"Venetoclax + obinutuzumab (Ven-Obi) → duración fija 12 meses","guid":"","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"CLL14 → SLP mediana 76.2 meses","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"139","text":"SG 6 años 78.7%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"139","text":"uMRD 76%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"138","text":"Venetoclax + ibrutinib → duración fija","guid":"","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"FLAIR → SLP superior a FCR, beneficio SG","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"143","text":"GLOW → SLP 42 meses 74.6%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"138","text":"Acalabrutinib ± obinutuzumab","guid":"","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"ELEVATE-TN → SLP 72 meses 78% (con Obi)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"138","text":"Zanubrutinib","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"138","text":"FCR → opción en jóvenes fit SIN disfunción p53","guid":"","children":[{"id":"150","parent":"149","text":"Potencial CURA FUNCIONAL en IGHV mutado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"149","text":"SLP mediana 14.6 años (IGHV-M)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"149","text":"Seguimiento 19 años MD Anderson","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"137","text":"IGHV NO MUTADO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"Acalabrutinib ± obinutuzumab","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"Zanubrutinib","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"Ibrutinib","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"153","text":"Venetoclax + ibrutinib","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"153","text":"Venetoclax + obinutuzumab","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"134","text":"CON del(17p)/mut TP53","guid":"","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"EVITAR inmunoquimioterapia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"BTKi solo o combinado con venetoclax","guid":"","children":[{"id":"162","parent":"161","text":"Ibrutinib, acalabrutinib, zanubrutinib","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"163","parent":"159","text":"Venetoclax + obinutuzumab","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"159","text":"Idelalisib + rituximab → solo si contraindicación a otros","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"159","text":"Considerar alo-TPH en segunda recaída","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"0","text":"AGENTES TERAPÉUTICOS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"INHIBIDORES DE BTK","guid":"","children":[{"id":"168","parent":"167","text":"Mecanismo → bloqueo señalización BCR → apoptosis + redistribución linfocitaria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"167","text":"Ibrutinib (1ª generación)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"170","parent":"169","text":"Irreversible, covalente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"169","text":"ORR 71-95%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"169","text":"Toxicidad OFF-TARGET → FA, ICC, sangrado, HTA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"169","text":"Resistencia → mut C481S BTK, mut PLCγ2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"169","text":"Monitorización cardiovascular OBLIGATORIA","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"175","parent":"167","text":"Acalabrutinib (2ª generación)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"176","parent":"175","text":"Más selectivo que ibrutinib","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"175","text":"MENOR tasa FA/flutter, sangrado, HTA (ELEVATE-RR)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"175","text":"100 mg c/12h","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"179","parent":"167","text":"Zanubrutinib (2ª generación)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"180","parent":"179","text":"Superior a ibrutinib en SLP (ALPINE)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"179","text":"MENOR toxicidad cardíaca","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"179","text":"160 mg c/12h","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"183","parent":"167","text":"Pirtobrutinib (NO covalente, reversible)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"184","parent":"183","text":"Activo contra mut C481S","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"183","text":"ORR 62% post-BTKi covalente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"183","text":"SIN FA grado 3 en estudios","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"183","text":"200 mg/día","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"188","parent":"167","text":"Degradadores de BTK (PROTACs) → en desarrollo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"189","parent":"188","text":"NX-5948 → fase 1a/b","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"188","text":"BGB-16673 → fase 1","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"188","text":"NX-2127 → degradador dual BTK + IKZF1/3","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"192","parent":"166","text":"INHIBIDORES DE BCL-2","guid":"","children":[{"id":"193","parent":"192","text":"Venetoclax","guid":"","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"Mimético BH3 → bloquea proteína anti-apoptótica Bcl-2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"193","text":"Ramp-up OBLIGATORIO (riesgo lisis tumoral)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"196","parent":"195","text":"20 → 50 → 100 → 200 → 400 mg semanal","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"197","parent":"193","text":"Dosis mantención 400 mg/día","guid":"wU1P-Iymskevv8o9y2Tabg","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"193","text":"ORR 79% en R/R del(17p)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"193","text":"EA principales → neutropenia (40%), infección (20%), anemia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"193","text":"Síndrome lisis tumoral → prevención con hidratación + monitorización","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"201","parent":"166","text":"ANTICUERPOS\\NANTI-CD20","guid":"IJQvr9uIYqXerouXY0VP0w","children":[{"id":"202","parent":"201","text":"Rituximab →\\Nquimérico, tipo I","guid":"itn8gVzgKca3atFD5TEjAw","children":[{"id":"203","parent":"202","text":"Poco activo como monoterapia en LLC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"202","text":"Potente en combinación (FCR, Ven-R)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"205","parent":"201","text":"Obinutuzumab (GA101) → humanizado, glicoingeniería","guid":"","children":[{"id":"206","parent":"205","text":"Mayor ADCC, menor CDC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"205","text":"Superior a rituximab (CLL11 → beneficio SG)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"208","parent":"201","text":"Ofatumumab → retirado del mercado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"209","parent":"166","text":"INHIBIDORES\\NDE PI3K","guid":"O5iDXaR6VqXhT4Yig2bDyQ","children":[{"id":"210","parent":"209","text":"Idelalisib (PI3Kδ) → aprobado con rituximab en R/R","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"209","text":"Duvelisib (PI3Kδ/γ)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"209","text":"Toxicidad clase → diarrea/colitis, hepatotoxicidad, neumonitis, infecciones oportunistas (CMV, PJP)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"209","text":"USO REDUCIDO por perfil de toxicidad","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"214","parent":"166","text":"INMUNOQUIMIOTERAPIA\\N(HISTÓRICA, USO DECRECIENTE)","guid":"wBxe3j9bVQ_5gv9AnN9Izg","children":[{"id":"215","parent":"214","text":"FCR → fludarabina + ciclofosfamida + rituximab","guid":"","children":[{"id":"216","parent":"215","text":"Gold standard histórico en jóvenes fit","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"215","text":"CLL8 → primer ensayo con beneficio SG en 1L","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"215","text":"Cura funcional en IGHV mutado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"219","parent":"214","text":"BR → bendamustina + rituximab","guid":"","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"Alternativa en >65 años","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"221","parent":"214","text":"Clb-Obi → clorambucilo + obinutuzumab","guid":"","children":[{"id":"222","parent":"221","text":"Pacientes comórbidos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"223","parent":"166","text":"TERAPIAS\\NCELULARES","guid":"AdnwOkHQVxgrHLp7hOl8Mg","children":[{"id":"224","parent":"223","text":"CAR-T\\Nanti-CD19","guid":"JQ9TlCnSGS7oLmFMI6xCUg","children":[{"id":"225","parent":"224","text":"ORR 44-74% en R/R","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"224","text":"Limitado por disfunción T en LLC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"224","text":"Ibrutinib mejora eficacia CAR-T","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"224","text":"Liso-cel → TRANSCEND CLL 004","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"229","parent":"223","text":"Alo-TPH → opción curativa en seleccionados","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"230","parent":"0","text":"TRATAMIENTO DE\\NSEGUNDA LÍNEA","guid":"0TysVajQ_9vvUrFmQiB_lg","children":[{"id":"231","parent":"230","text":"REGLA GENERAL → repetir 1L si remisión >3-4 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"230","text":"Recaída precoz (<3-4 años) o refractaria → cambiar clase","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"230","text":"Post-BTKi → Ven + rituximab/obinutuzumab (hasta 2 años)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"234","parent":"233","text":"Si mut C481S → ncBTKi (pirtobrutinib)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"235","parent":"230","text":"Post-Ven-Obi → BTKi ± anti-CD20","guid":"","children":[{"id":"236","parent":"235","text":"Si remisión >3-4 años → repetir Ven-Obi","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"237","parent":"230","text":"Post-inmunoquimioterapia → BTKi o Ven-R/Ven-Obi","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"238","parent":"0","text":"DOBLE\\NREFRACTARIEDAD\\N(2R)","guid":"l9hOGoelB-mgaZnvLuWXsw","children":[{"id":"239","parent":"238","text":"Definición → refractario a BTKi Y BCL2i","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"238","text":"Problema EMERGENTE con uso creciente de agentes dirigidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"238","text":"SG mediana 8-27 meses en 2R pretratado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"238","text":"Escenarios que llevan a 2R","guid":"","children":[{"id":"243","parent":"242","text":"1L BTKi continuo → 2L Ven combo → resistencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"244","parent":"242","text":"1L Ven-CD20 fija → 2L BTKi → resistencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"242","text":"1L Ven+BTKi fija → recaída con doble exposición","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"246","parent":"238","text":"Opciones aprobadas limitadas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"247","parent":"246","text":"PI3Ki (idelalisib + rituximab) → eficacia modesta, toxicidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"248","parent":"246","text":"Pirtobrutinib → ORR 70% post-cBTKi, SLP mediana 16.8 meses","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"249","parent":"238","text":"Opciones experimentales","guid":"","children":[{"id":"250","parent":"249","text":"Degradadores de BTK","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"251","parent":"249","text":"Nuevos BCL2i e inhibidores MCL1","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"252","parent":"249","text":"Anticuerpos anti-ROR1 (zilovertamab)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"253","parent":"249","text":"BsAbs/BiTEs → epcoritamab (CD3×CD20) → ORR 53% en doble-expuesto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"254","parent":"249","text":"CAR-T cells","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"249","text":"Estrategias de remodelación del microambiente tumoral","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"256","parent":"0","text":"TRANSFORMACIÓN\\NDE RICHTER","guid":"ZHlHZ-fXaM3S_diP7549yQ","children":[{"id":"257","parent":"256","text":"Linfoma difuso de células B grandes → origen clonal LLC","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"258","parent":"256","text":"→ segunda neoplasia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"259","parent":"256","text":"Mediana supervivencia 3.5 meses post-progresión en BTKi","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"260","parent":"256","text":"Tratamiento →\\Ncheckpoint inhibitors\\N+ BTKi o BCL2i","guid":"GhvSdwtkABiyJcNtOsGQJQ","children":[{"id":"261","parent":"260","text":"Tislelizumab + zanubrutinib → RT1 → ORR 58.3%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"262","parent":"260","text":"Atezolizumab + venetoclax + obinutuzumab → MOLTO → ORR 67.9%","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"263","parent":"0","text":"SOPORTE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"264","parent":"263","text":"Vacunas → actualizar esquema (respuesta subóptima)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"265","parent":"263","text":"Hipogammaglobulinemia sintomática → Ig EV de reemplazo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"266","parent":"263","text":"Profilaxis infecciones oportunistas según tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"267","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"268","parent":"267","text":"LLC es enfermedad del ADULTO MAYOR → mediana diagnóstico 70 años → SIEMPRE considerar comorbilidades y fragilidad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"269","parent":"267","text":"del(17p)/mut TP53 → NUNCA inmunoquimioterapia → BTKi o venetoclax","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"270","parent":"267","text":"Watch and wait en estadios tempranos asintomáticos → NO tratar NO es NO hacer → seguimiento activo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"271","parent":"267","text":"Ramp-up de venetoclax OBLIGATORIO → riesgo lisis tumoral en primeras dosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"272","parent":"267","text":"BTKi 2ª gen (acalabrutinib/zanubrutinib) preferibles a ibrutinib → menor toxicidad cardiovascular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"273","parent":"267","text":"FCR aún puede curar LLC IGHV mutado sin disfunción p53 → seguimiento 19 años lo confirma","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"274","parent":"267","text":"uMRD predice desenlaces → guía duración de tratamiento con agentes dirigidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"275","parent":"267","text":"Doble refractariedad (2R) → problema emergente sin estándar → derivar a protocolos experimentales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"276","parent":"267","text":"Linfocitosis aislada e hipogammaglobulinemia aislada NO indican tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"277","parent":"267","text":"Monitorización cardiovascular con TODO BTKi → FA, HTA, sangrado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"278","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIÉN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"279","parent":"278","text":"→ Polifarmacia en AM (Geriatría)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"280","parent":"278","text":"→ Fragilidad y Valoración Geriátrica (Geriatría)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"281","parent":"278","text":"→ Valoración Geriátrica Integral (Geriatría)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"282","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"283","parent":"282","text":"1. Hallek M. Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia: 2025 Update on the Epidemiology, Pathogenesis, Diagnosis, and Therapy. Am J Hematol. 2025;100:450-480.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"284","parent":"282","text":"2. Hallek M, Cheson BD, Catovsky D, et al. iwCLL Guidelines for Diagnosis, Indications for Treatment, Response Assessment, and Supportive Management of CLL. Blood. 2018;131:2745-2760.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"285","parent":"282","text":"3. Döhner H, Stilgenbauer S, Benner A, et al. Genomic Aberrations and Survival in Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia. N Engl J Med. 2000;343:1910-1916.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"286","parent":"282","text":"4. Fischer K, Al-Sawaf O, Bahlo J, et al. Venetoclax and Obinutuzumab in Patients With CLL and Coexisting Conditions. N Engl J Med. 2019;380:2225-2236.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"287","parent":"282","text":"5. Al-Sawaf O, Robrecht S, Zhang C, et al. Venetoclax-Obinutuzumab for Previously Untreated CLL: 6-Year Results of the CLL14 Study. Blood. 2024;144:1924-1935.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"288","parent":"282","text":"6. Munir T, Cairns DA, Bloor A, et al. CLL Therapy Guided by Measurable Residual Disease. N Engl J Med. 2024;390:326-337.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"289","parent":"282","text":"7. Eichhorst B, Niemann CU, Kater AP, et al. First-Line Venetoclax Combinations in CLL. N Engl J Med. 2023;388:1739-1754.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"290","parent":"282","text":"8. Brown JR, Eichhorst B, Hillmen P, et al. Zanubrutinib or Ibrutinib in Relapsed or Refractory CLL. N Engl J Med. 2023;388:319-332.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"291","parent":"282","text":"9. Thompson PA, Bazinet A, Wierda WG, et al. Sustained Remissions in CLL After Frontline FCR With Very-Long-Term Follow-Up. Blood. 2023;142:1784-1788.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"292","parent":"282","text":"10. International CLL IPI Working Group. An International Prognostic Index for Patients With CLL (CLL-IPI). Lancet Oncol. 2016;17:779-790.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":292,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"LLC 2025 Hallek iPad","id":"map_799","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"LLC 2025 Hallek iPad"}